&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b4&lt;/b&gt; reads &lt;i&gt;\(papyä)tk(u) ṣāmne wsāl tāṣ kätko ka‹t›iṃ wsāli(s)///&lt;/i&gt; in [[Carling, DThTA]]: 121 (TI)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Translation from [[Ogihara 2009]]: 200-201:&lt;br&gt;
a1 which he is shown then, that (law) is to be employed. ///&lt;br&gt;
a2 2 || The clothes for the monk is arised, (and ... of Kaṭhina-clothes has passed) ///&lt;br&gt;
a3 for ten nights [finally] ///&lt;br&gt;
a4 If he seize (it) for more than this, the clothes are to be turned ///&lt;br&gt;
b1 (confession) is to be made. 1 The clothes for the monk is arised, (and ... of Kaṭhina-clothes has passed) ///&lt;br&gt;
b2 for one night, separate from three clothes ///&lt;br&gt;
b3 (except for) [the agreement] (of the community), the clothes are to be turned ///&lt;br&gt;
b4 The clothes for the monk is arised, (and ... of Kaṭhina-clothes has passed) ///&lt;/p&gt;</item>
